<!-- Calibration Help Modal -->
<div class="help-modal-backdrop" id="helpModal">
    <div class="help-modal">
        <button class="help-close" id="helpClose">&times;</button>
        <h2>Meter Calibration Help</h2>

        <h3>Overview</h3>
        <p>Each meter has a calibration table that maps the raw values your radio reports (0&ndash;255) to real-world display values. The app interpolates between your calibration points to give smooth, accurate readings across the full scale.</p>

        <h3>The Calibration Page</h3>
        <p>Each meter card shows:</p>
        <ul>
            <li><strong>Gauge</strong> &mdash; live needle updated from the radio every 750ms</li>
            <li><strong>Raw</strong> &mdash; the raw value (0&ndash;255) currently reported by the radio</li>
            <li><strong>Calibrated</strong> &mdash; the display value your current calibration produces</li>
            <li><strong>Calibration points</strong> &mdash; a table of Raw Value / Radio Value pairs</li>
            <li><strong>Add Point</strong> &mdash; adds a new calibration point</li>
            <li><strong>&times;</strong> &mdash; removes a calibration point</li>
            <li><strong>Save</strong> &mdash; saves this individual meter</li>
        </ul>

        <h3>How Calibration Works</h3>
        <table>
            <tr><th>Raw Value</th><th>Radio Value</th></tr>
            <tr><td>Number the radio reports (0&ndash;255)</td><td>Real-world value you want displayed</td></tr>
        </table>
        <p>The app draws a straight line between adjacent points. The more points you add, the more accurately it follows your meter's curve.</p>

        <h3>Calibrating the Power Meter</h3>
        <ol>
            <li>Set your radio to a known power level (e.g. 5W)</li>
            <li>Press <strong>TX</strong> on this page to transmit</li>
            <li>Note the <strong>Raw</strong> value shown on the Power card</li>
            <li>Press <strong>TX</strong> again to stop</li>
            <li>Enter that Raw value and <strong>5</strong> as the Radio Value</li>
            <li>Repeat at several power levels to build a curve</li>
            <li>Click <strong>Save</strong> on the Power card</li>
        </ol>

        <h3>Calibrating the S-Meter</h3>
        <p>Radio Values for the S-Meter are labels (S1, S2 &hellip; S9, +10, +20, +40) rather than numbers.</p>
        <p>The easiest method uses the <strong>RF/SQL control</strong> &mdash; the outer ring on the knob next to the Multi knob on the FTdx101MP. Rotating this ring lets you smoothly reduce the S-meter reading and stop the needle at any point.</p>
        <p>First reduce background noise as much as possible:</p>
        <ul>
            <li><strong>Best:</strong> Connect the radio to a dummy load</li>
            <li><strong>Next best:</strong> Disconnect the antenna</li>
            <li><strong>Worst:</strong> Find the quietest frequency you can</li>
        </ul>
        <ol>
            <li>Rotate the RF/SQL outer ring slowly &mdash; watch the <strong>Raw</strong> value on the S-Meter card drop</li>
            <li>Stop when the radio's front panel S-meter shows a known level (e.g. S1)</li>
            <li>Enter that Raw value and <strong>S1</strong> as the Radio Value</li>
            <li>Rotate to the next S-meter step and repeat</li>
            <li>Work through S1, S2 &hellip; S9, and +10, +20, +40 if achievable</li>
            <li>Click <strong>Save</strong> on the S-Meter card when done</li>
        </ol>

        <h3>Calibrating SWR, ALC, IDD, VDD, Temperature</h3>
        <p>The process is the same for all numeric meters: transmit or observe the radio's front panel, note the Raw value, enter it with the known real-world value, and save.</p>

        <h3>Tips</h3>
        <ul>
            <li>The app ships with default calibration points &mdash; only adjust them if readings are inaccurate</li>
            <li>Always have a point near Raw=0 and one near the maximum you expect, to avoid off-scale readings</li>
            <li>Always transmit into a dummy load or antenna &mdash; never without a load connected</li>
            <li><strong>Reload From File</strong> discards unsaved changes and reloads the last saved calibration</li>
            <li><strong>Save Calibration</strong> (top button) saves all meters at once</li>
        </ul>

        <h3>Where Calibration Data Is Saved</h3>
        <ul>
            <li><strong>Installed app:</strong> %APPDATA%\MM5AGM\FTdx101\WebApp\calibration.user.json</li>
            <li><strong>Development:</strong> wwwroot/calibration.default.json</li>
        </ul>
        <p>The save path is shown at the top of this page.</p>
    </div>
</div>
